column2: fighting to break the mould that their mothers and grandmothers had often been forced into. she never limited herself to just as an actor

can be heard. she pushed for screen time on par with her male co-leads

column4: sree garu's life inspires us all to believe that our actions – however small – can lead to true progress🌷

column2: mentally and emotionally. this was was first time in three years i’ve been at peace during thanksgiving. •

column1: 217044;instagram;2018-11-24 18:33:38;FALSE;"the sign that i wore on my back at the first #womensmarch to reach out to other survivors
column2: so they might finally be able to forgive themselves for what was done to them
column3: and begin healing. 💖 ***trigger warning for survivors of sexual violence and abuse*** my favorite part of the march was when a very young girl approached me to thank me
column4: and very sheepishly asked if she could hug me! :') she could not have been more than fourteen years old (the age that i was when i was raped)... 💔

column2: my eyes filled with tears as they met her mother's who was standing just a few feet away
column3: and she mouthed the words ""thank you!"" 💜💜💜 it was never our fault.

column1: the shame belongs only to the perpetrators of abuse.
thank you for changing the world with us! 🔥💪🏼🦄🌎💖🔥 #bethechange

#darknesscannotsurvivelight ***trigger warning for survivor of sexual abuse*** ""they 'let you' do it..."" those words triggered my anxiety like a fireball to the chest... it felt like my stomach dropped down outside of my body
column4: and guilt) was back. ☹️ when targeted by a dangerous and/or powerful predator that is too strong to defeat
column5: our bodies are triggered to freeze... for survivors of domestic or sexual violence/abuse
column7: we know all too well what can happen when we are faced with the dilemma of trying not to escalate a situation where a violent person has decided that you are their target or prey. ☹️ please understand that survivors of abuse don't just ""'let them' (sexual predators or abusers) do anything""... they are having a natural response to intense trauma that they feel they can not escape safely
column8: and they are literally frozen in terror and shock.

column1: read and share this information to help us remove the stigma from survivors of sexual violence/assault/and abuse for ""not fighting back"". our brains and bodies literally preserved our safety and lives in a completely natural way.
don't be so hard on yourself if you froze when you were attacked. many people do. please don't be cruel to yourself anymore. no matter how many people have blamed you

column1: 217059;instagram;2018-11-24 17:42:44;FALSE;"resharing my experience of publicly identifying myself as a survivor of domestic and sexual violence
column2: and ptsd! 🔥🔥💪🏼🦄🔥🔥 exhausted and having a panic attack as i made my way into the park before the women’s march even began... it started in the car
column3: and for a few moments i was frozen and felt numb all over as we were getting dropped off.. it was difficult to get my legs to work as i was fighting to feel them again
column4: and it took me awhile to stand up on my trembling knees.

column1: as we made our way down the block
column2: i felt like someone cupped their hands over my ears
column3: and everything seemed muffled and surreal
column4: and i had the floating sensation. #dissociation

column1: i focused on my breathing to get more oxygen to my brain
column2: and to calm myself during the amygdala hijack.

column1: i began to ask myself questions to stimulate the parts of my brain that are not active when i am triggered
column3: and begin to force function there.

column2: while my heart pounded furiously inside my chest
column3: but as a survivor of abuse
column4: i learned to hide my panic well.. to hyperventilate softly
column5: and to appear dead calm while triggered
column6: in an attempt to keep my ex-abuser from using my reactions to his abuse as an excuse to get angry again
column7: and to ridicule me for having the kind of feelings with which he could never seem to understand or empathize.

column1: 217084;instagram;2018-11-24 01:23:21;FALSE;"2 more tattoos. the female symbol and grl pwr in my mom’s handwriting surrounded by a heart. (trigger warning: sexual assault)

column2: ever-more-educated intersectional feminism. they also represent some recently discovered personal strength and knowledge.

column1: it’s ok to not want a significant other right now or maybe ever. it’s ok to have been violated in the past. it’s ok to not trust almost anyone in order to protect yourself. it’s ok to not want to identify as a victim because it makes you sound pitiful
column2: but also want to identify as a victim because it wasn’t your goddamn fault.

column1: it has taken me a long time to realize the pervasive singlism i’ve experienced throughout my teen and adult years. and it took me just a short time to realize the reality of victim blaming after becoming the victim myself.
basically: treat others how you would want to be treated if you were in their shoes. and maybe realize that no one wants you to say things like
column2: “you just haven’t found the right person yet
column3: ” or “how could you not know it was rape at the time?” to them.

column1: thank you for attending my ted talk. 👏

column3: même si tu t'es déshabillée devant lui
column4: il n'avait pas le droit de te forcer. personne n'a le droit de rentrer en toi
column5: si tu ne le veux pas. tous les hommes ne sont pas comme ça. il y a des hommes qui t'auraient respectée. qui t'auraient écoutée. qui auraient su patienter.

column2: c'était lui. ce n'était pas toi. tu lui avais clairement dit non. suffisamment fort pour qu'il t'entende
column4: alors que c'est lui qui aurait dû te laisser. il a passé outre. alors si
column5: on peut dire ça: il t'a violée.

column4: que ta parole n'a pas d'importance
column5: que ton opinion de sert à rien: tout cela a été implanté dans ton cerveau à ce moment-là.

column2: et tu mérites d'en connaître bien d'autres encore. tu mérites de parvenir
column4: de te réjouir. ton avenir est à toi. ton corps est à toi. ne laisse pas le monstre t'enlever tout cela. il a déjà fait tant de dégâts.

column2: si cette prise de conscience s'effectue
column3: c'est parce que tu es assez forte pour les affronter

217169;instagram;2018-11-24 16:06:59;FALSE;women power is at its peak now which has given courage to at least a small percentage of women to break their silence over the assault on their dignity. and it is always said that better late than never. now it can said that the #metoo movement has truly arrived in india and it will have an impact not only on powerful men to pay for their mistakes but also force the government to amend the laws.

the reason for intiation of #metoo movement is the failure of our judicial system to provide quick justice. victims who have written formal complaints and tried to get their organisation to act have mostly found themselves facing a system that prefers to be complicit with the perpetrators. the failure of due process/ law is the success of #metoo.

lastly many people especially men have raised concerns regarding false accusations. this is valid no movement is perfect and all battles have collateral damage. this makes it important that men instead of beating their chests about potential victimhood
column2: actively ally in making the system a functional one in which all victims including those of false allegations can seek justice.

column1: 217182;instagram;2018-11-24 16:14:08;FALSE;"experts recommend seeking medical help as soon as possible after the event
column2: preferred in the first 96 hours of the attack. even if you do not plan to report the attack to law enforcement
column3: experts still can conduct a forensic exam to collect evidence if you wish to prosecute the offender in the future. you can choose which parts of the exam you consent to and which parts you do. they suggest this because testable evidence is recoverable for adults within 96 hours or 72 hours for a child under 13
column4: if you had not washed before the exam there's a higher chance of evidence. if attending the hospital they ask for the clothes the attack happened in. after all the exam has been complete they give you toiletries to wash and clothing to wear home from the hospital. nurses will collect many forms of evidence depending on needs ( urine
column8: you will then be offered medication to prevent stis and emergency contraception
column9: it is ultimately your decision whether you take it or not. you will also be best attending hospital because they should test to make sure no physical harm has came to you and to prevent/stop it.

column1: 217184;instagram;2018-11-24 16:15:07;FALSE;"there are many ways to support a rape survivor and here are a few: (feel free to add or/and share  your opinions in the comments)
a) listen- try not to interrupt no matter how many questions you have
column2: show you're listening and you care. this should make them feel supported and better about being able to share with someone.

column1: b) let them stay in control- they felt powerless once before and they may need to have some direction but they should be as free and as comfortable as they need.
c) be patient and understanding- many survivors feel a lack of trust towards people
column2: if they trust you it took them time and you must have a strong bond with them. they may take time and you should let them take as much time as they need as long as they are not endangering themselves or others.

column1: d) believe them- people rarely lie
e) know it's not their fault- don't victim blame
f) recognise their courage-it took a lot for them to be strong and carry on.
g) don't ignore the attack but don't just talk about it- they may want to move on and need help all at once
column2: they will take their time to talk and do what they need.

column3: maar al snel ging het beter #goteam in de rust hadden we een lekker kopje thee (het was koud in de sahara) en hadden we een tussenstand van 0-3. in de tweede helft werd het agressieniveau van de wedstrijd opgevoerd en daarnaast gingen we al beter spelen. al redelijk snel viel er een goal voor ons! column1: 217198;instagram;2018-07-13 17:43:39;FALSE;i’m so very grateful for my support system. however
column2: i know (because it’s been said) that my support system doesn’t understand what i’m going through. i want to be strong and decisive enough to close this god forsaken book of shit in my life but i can’t seem to find a way in which to access my firmness and loyalty to myself and do what i know needs to be done. instead
column3: i become silently irritated by my family’s calls with invites to everything from family gatherings to school functions to helping out at their business functions. i know that it’s done with the best intentions (just to get me out and away from him even if momentarily) but my goodness my entire body feels as it’s 1000 lbs in weight and my inability to say no taunts me. the stress is unbearable and frustrating. the hell i’m  living is within myself. how does one get out of this shit hole when you are your worst enemy? #npd #narcnomore #emotionalabuse #verbalabuse #mentalabuse #digitalabuse #physicalabuse #financialabuse #infidelity #lies #manipulation #gaslighting #projection #controlling #metoo #npd_uncovered overed;;en;#npd

column3: ‘the concept of human rights’ with mr. shehara herath at imperial college of business studies

column1: giving an insightful journey down the history
column2: where 70 years ago the universal declaration of human rights
column3: the global document which influenced legal protection of human rights was established
column4: mr. shehara herath discussed the fundamental rights all of us have but aren't aware of.
we all are united under one factor. that is human rights. but still
column6: just as it was back then
column7: these rights are violated by authorities where people who aren't aware of the rights they possess
column8: become vulnerable and hence keep silent.

column1: this engaging session enlightened us on our rights and guided us on how to assert them whenever they are violated.
we are grateful to mr. shehara herath for dedicating his time for such an insightful evening and we

column2: sunday november 25th is the international day for the elimination of violence against women.

column1: if you read my last post you’ll know why this issue is so personally important to me. having experienced the violence i have
column2: and having had access to resources to heal from it
column3: i feel that i have a responsibility to talk about this issue. my hope is that by bringing awareness to it we can start the process of reducing and eliminating violence against women and girls.

column1: let’s start by getting clear about what it is. according to @unwomen
column2: violence against women and girls manifest in physical

column1: ❌sexual violence and harassment ❌human trafficking ❌female genital mutilation
all of these have devastating consequences well beyond the incidents themselves. and they all deny women and girls of their basic human right to safety.

people might think it’s not a big deal to harass a woman walking down the street. but even these incidents can make us feel physically unsafe and emotionally depleted. how can we ever be expected to thrive in work or in school if we’re constantly made to feel like this? how can we ever feel secure and supported enough to share our thoughts and ideas? how can we ever truly honor our potential in such an oppressive environment? 💔
the heartbreaking truth is that we can’t. 💔
which is why it’s essential for us
column3: to do the important work of acknowledging and changing the way we treat the female members of our society. 👑

column1: women and girls have so much to offer this world. and the persistent and pervasive violence against us deprives our culture of our gifts
column2: our potential and our power. we have a moral
column5: obligation to end violence against women and girls. it will not be easy. but it is urgently necessary.

column2: as opposed to societal obstacles which are the real burden to disabled people. when you 'other' a group of people
column3: human rights are not seen as necessary for that group.

column1: men denna depressionen kunde jag inte klara mig ur på egen hand.
efter att min mamma och vänner hade övertalat mig om att jag borde prata med någon svalde jag min stolthet o gick o tog
jag fick genast en bra kontakt med personen som jag pratade med på psykosociala enheten.
hon visade förståelse och hjälpte mig att sätta känslor på händelser som jag inte har kunnat förstå själv.
jag är oerhört glad idag över att jag gjorde det.
dåliga minnen kom tillbaka som jag hade förträngt.
men dem fick mig till att förstå mig själv bättre.
jag slutade att gå till henne i mitten av oktober.
min olycka för 6 år sedan fick mig att vakna upp och se livet ur ett annat och bättre perspektiv.
jag ville bara komma snabbare in till stan just den där kvällen.
för att jag hade blivit osams med folk på festen som jag var på.

min olycka har lett mig till platser som jag idag är oerhört tacksam över.
alla underbara människor som jag har träffat.
sprid kärlek till alla för att du vet aldrig hur en människa mår.

column1: 217484;instagram;2018-11-24 10:24:03;FALSE;"नजरिया👇👇👇 *करीब के गाँव में दो सहेलियाँ 12 वीं की परीक्षा देने जा रही हैं और चलते हुए आपस में बातें कर रही हैं।*👇 सीता---: गीता
column2: तू तो बिल्कुल भी पढ़ाई नहीं करती है। गीता -- छोड़ न यार! पास हुए तो फिर 13
column4: 15 वीं की परीक्षा दो और फिर नौकरी वाला पति....😳 सीता-- : तो ? बढ़िया तो है। गीता--: क्या बढ़िया है ?  12 घंटों की नौकरी और तनख्वाह 25-30 हजार। फिर मुंबई-पूना जैसे बड़े शहरों में रहने जाओ। वहाँ किराए का घर होगा जिसमें आधी तनख्वाह चली जाएगी। फिर अपना खुदका घर चाहिए तो लोन लेकर 4-5 मंजिल ऊपर घर लो और एक गुफा जैसे बंद घर में रहो। लोन चुकाने में 15-20 साल लगेंगे और बड़ी किल्लत में गृहस्थी चलेगी। न त्यौहारों में छुट्टी न गर्मी में। सदा बीमारी का घर। स्वस्थ रहना हो तो ऑर्गेनिक के नाम पर 3-4 गुना कीमत देकर सामान खरीदो। और फाइनली वो नौकरी करने वाला नौकर ही तो होगा। तू सारा जोड़ घटाना गुणा भाग करले
column5: तेरी समझ में आ जाएगा। घर का खर्च नहीं चल पाया तो तुझे भी नौकरी करणी पडेगी...😫 और अगर परीक्षा में फेल हो गई तो किसी खेती किसानी वाले किसान से ब्याह दी जाउँगी। जीवन थोड़ा तकलीफदेह तो होगा लेकिन वो खुद का सच्चा मालिक होगा और मैं होऊँगी मालकिन। पैसे कम ज्यादा होंगे लेकिन सारे अपने होंगे
column6: कोई टेक्स का लफड़ा नहीं। सारा कुछ ऑर्गेनिक उपजाएँगे और वही खाएँगे। बीमारी की चिंता फिक्र ही नहीं
column8: पति 24 घंटे अपने साथ ही रहेगा। बाद में #metoo #metoo कर पछताणे का भी कोई चांस नहीं। सीता--- : मैं भी फेल ही हो जाती हूँ रे.....!!

column4: 15 वीं की परीक्षा दो और फिर नौकरी वाला पति ... .😳 सीता -- : तो ? बढ़िया तो है। गीता -- : क्या बढ़िया है ? 12 घंटों की नौकरी और तनख्वाह 25-30 हजार। फिर मुंबई-पूना जैसे बड़े शहरों में रहने जाओ। वहाँ किराए का घर होगा जिसमें आधी तनख्वाह चली जाएगी। फिर अपना खुदका घर चाहिए तो लोन लेकर 4-5 मंजिल ऊपर घर लो और एक गुफा जैसे बंद घर में रहो। लोन चुकाने में 15-20 साल लगेंगे और बड़ी किल्लत में गृहस्थी चलेगी। न त्यौहारों में छुट्टी न गर्मी में। सदा बीमारी का घर। स्वस्थ रहना हो तो ऑर्गेनिक के नाम पर 3-4 गुना कीमत देकर सामान खरीदो। और फाइनली वो नौकरी करने वाला नौकर ही तो होगा। तू सारा जोड़ घटाना गुणा भाग करले
column5: तेरी समझ में आ जाएगा। घर का खर्च नहीं चल पाया तो तुझे भी नौकरी करणी पडेगी ... 😫 और अगर परीक्षा में फेल हो गई तो किसी खेती किसानी वाले किसान से ब्याह दी जाउँगी। जीवन थोड़ा तकलीफदेह तो होगा लेकिन वो खुद का सच्चा मालिक होगा और मैं होऊँगी मालकिन। पैसे कम ज्यादा होंगे लेकिन सारे अपने होंगे
column6: कोई टेक्स का लफड़ा नहीं। सारा कुछ ऑर्गेनिक उपजाएँगे और वही खाएँगे। बीमारी की चिंता फिक्र ही नहीं
column8: पति 24 घंटे अपने साथ ही रहेगा। बाद में कर पछताणे का भी कोई चांस नहीं। सीता -- - : मैं भी फेल ही हो जाती हूँ रे ... .. ! ! 😜😜 ;[('नजरिया👇👇👇'

column1: 217486;instagram;2018-11-24 10:25:01;FALSE;"અમદાવાદની મુલાકાતે આવેલા આ ફિલ્મકારે કહ્યું હા હું મોદીનો સમર્થક છું..............

અમદાવાદની ખાનગી કોલેજમાં હાજરી આપવા આવેલા વિવેક અગ્નિહોત્રીની nsui નેતાઓએ ગાડી રોકવાનો પ્રયાસ કર્યો હતો. અને ફુલ ફેંકીને વિરોધ દર્શાવ્યો હતો. આ સમયે પોલીસ અને nsui વચ્ચે ઝપાઝપી પણ થઇ હતી. કાર્યક્રમ દરમિયાન વિવેક અગ્નિહોત્રીએ mee too અંતર્ગત તેમનાં પર થયેલા આક્ષેપોને નકાર્યા હતા. આક્ષેપ કરનાર પર તેમણે ક્રિમિનલ ડિફરમેશન કેસ કર્યો છે. તેમણે કહ્યું કે mee too સારું અભિયાન છે. પણ તેનો મિસ યુઝ ન થવો જોઈએ.

#ahmedabad #vivkeagnihotri #support #pm #narindermodi #and #metoo #campine #news #gstv";"અમદાવાદની મુલાકાતે આવેલા આ ફિલ્મકારે કહ્યું હા હું મોદીનો સમર્થક છું..............

અમદાવાદની ખાનગી કોલેજમાં હાજરી આપવા આવેલા વિવેક અગ્નિહોત્રીની nsui નેતાઓએ ગાડી રોકવાનો પ્રયાસ કર્યો હતો. અને ફુલ ફેંકીને વિરોધ દર્શાવ્યો હતો. આ સમયે પોલીસ અને nsui વચ્ચે ઝપાઝપી પણ થઇ હતી. કાર્યક્રમ દરમિયાન વિવેક અગ્નિહોત્રીએ mee too અંતર્ગત તેમનાં પર થયેલા આક્ષેપોને નકાર્યા હતા. આક્ષેપ કરનાર પર તેમણે ક્રિમિનલ ડિફરમેશન કેસ કર્યો છે. તેમણે કહ્યું કે mee too સારું અભિયાન છે. પણ તેનો મિસ યુઝ ન થવો જોઈએ.

";અમદાવાદની મુલાકાતે આવેલા આ ફિલ્મકારે કહ્યું હા હું મોદીનો સમર્થક છું ... ... ... ... .. ... ... ... અમદાવાદની ખાનગી કોલેજમાં હાજરી આપવા આવેલા વિવેક અગ્નિહોત્રીની nsui નેતાઓએ ગાડી રોકવાનો પ્રયાસ કર્યો હતો . અને ફુલ ફેંકીને વિરોધ દર્શાવ્યો હતો . આ સમયે પોલીસ અને nsui વચ્ચે ઝપાઝપી પણ થઇ હતી . કાર્યક્રમ દરમિયાન વિવેક અગ્નિહોત્રીએ mee અંતર્ગત તેમનાં પર થયેલા આક્ષેપોને નકાર્યા હતા . આક્ષેપ કરનાર પર તેમણે ક્રિમિનલ ડિફરમેશન કેસ કર્યો છે . તેમણે કહ્યું કે mee સારું અભિયાન છે . પણ તેનો મિસ યુઝ ન થવો જોઈએ . ;[('અમદાવાદની'

column1: 217492;instagram;2018-11-24 10:29:31;FALSE;"to all you girls out there who come to mumbai with dreams in your eyes and passion in your heart
column2: don't let the demonic stories that you read deter you from pursuing your dreams. the dark side of the coin is that these men exist everywhere
column3: in nearly every field of work where both sexes are meant to work together. they are those men who assume that a woman in the glam industry must unquestionably be willing to give sexual favours in return for work.

column1: making sexual advances and asking for sexual favours is the man's audacity; but having the firmness to say no and to move forward holding your head up high
column2: having the confidence that good work and genuine folks will come your way is the woman's audaciousness.

column4: maka dapat mendorong terciptanya peraturan yang berpihak pada korban  dan mewujudkan masyarakat yang anti kekerasan.

column1: 217539;instagram;2018-11-24 09:27:24;FALSE;"京都にある性被害の自助グループ「mint（ミント）」12月の活動予定のお知らせです❤︎
女性として生きる中で感じていることを気軽に話せる場所です。批判やアドバイスはせず、話すほうも聞くほうもお互いにありのままで受け止めます。主に性的なトラウマを抱える女性を対象としていますが、性被害のご経験の有無に関わらず女性として生きてきた中で向き合いたいことやお話ししたいことがあるときに足を運んでみてくださいね。
京都駅中央改札口より徒歩約12分
参加ご希望の方は下記①〜④の事項を添えてメールにてお申し込みください。折り返しご連絡いたします。
①メールの件名「ミント参加希望」
②お名前（ニックネーム可）
会場へのアクセスなど自助グループについて詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「self help group」をご覧ください。
遠方の方や直接会うことに抵抗がある場合はオンラインサロンでもお話しすることができます。月に1回のミーティングのほか、お気に入りの音楽や写真をアップしたり自分の体験を綴ったり、ネット上に開設した当事者のためのサロンです。
オンラインサロンについての詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「online salon」をご覧ください。
お話しできることを楽しみにしています(*^^*)

column1: 217654;instagram;2018-11-24 05:45:41;FALSE;"「 性犯罪 ・性暴力被害 者への対応に関する請願書 」に
ご賛同くださった皆様への報告
2018年11月22日、埼玉県知事特別秘書に対して
皆様からの請願書を提出して参りました。
631筆の署名をお預かりいたしました。
1、24時間対応の予算を組んで欲しいこと
(予算編成の時期なので是非)
2.まずは周知がすすんでいないので、周知に努めてもらいたいこと。
3.対応できる病院が6ヶ所と少ないので増やして欲しいこと
4.相談員の資質の充実を図って欲しいこと。
等などをお話しして参りました。
皆さまからの請願を真摯に受け止め
24時間対応の予算について検討し
結果をご連絡いたしますと、返答がありました。
結果の報告があり次第、
皆様にお伝えする予定です。
引き続き、関心の目を向け
皆が平穏な生活を営むことが出来る社会を実現させましょう。引き続きのご協力をどうぞよろしくお願いいたします。
#性犯罪 #性暴力 #性暴力被害者支援  #請願書  #埼玉県 #埼玉県知事 #埼玉県知事特別秘書 #署名 #予算 #病院 #24時間 #報告

column1: 217735;instagram;2018-11-24 01:41:43;FALSE;"silence & surrender [neon] is the hallmark marquee and opening track in “painted holograms” the lp and a follow up to the original debut single. there were a lot of bejeweled
column2: rich elements to both original song and music video that touch psychological nerves
column3: which we wanted to revisit and explore over and over.  the video is the most daring piece i have executed to date

column2: it’s benevolent sexism—yes it’s a thing and worth a conversation as confusing
column3: maddening and disappointing examples are popping up a lot lately. ‘benevolent sexism’ is where women—who benefit from the patriarchy—defend and maintain its sexist gender roles—the ones where men take care of women
column4: and women depend on men to take care of them
column5: outside the home. think betsy devos pushing college sexual assault reporting rules “narrowing the definition for what counts as sexual misconduct
column6: creating barriers for students to report these incidents and limiting the responsibility of schools to respond
column8: and the the women senators who voted for kavanaugh. now that we know what it is {wtf!} if we can name it

column5: despite my family descending into nothingness around me and she leaving behind an unfinished university dissertation about rape crisis. i've held firm to my virtues even when the material world wouldn't purchase what i had to offer them. i've seen horrors and absolute beauty
column6: all in the same day while backpacking vietnam. yes

column1: 217822;instagram;2018-11-23 23:04:06;FALSE;"i am a sexual assault survivor and i’m not proud of it actually.
i was 12 years old and he was my boyfriend (1 year difference). it happened twice
column2: once in his room and once in my room. i wasn’t drugged
column3: drunk or stoned. remembering every horrible detail from the touching to the pain he gave me is a burden i will carry with me forever and it’s a shame. i want you all to know that if something like this happen go to the police! i regret that i never did that. he will never see the truth. i see him every day on the way of school
column4: or him talking to my friends
column5: saying i need to get over it. that will never happen unfortunately.

column1: to my “friends” that say i understand. you don’t. it’s that simple. i remember everything and you talking about thinks like: “i know for sure you masturbate” or other things like that is rude and painful. i can’t enjoy relationships or intimacy. i don’t want sex or masturbation because of that. being convinced and thinking you know my story better then me is the reason why i don’t talk about it. stop saying shit you have no clue about.
to my followers: i’m here for you. i’m available 24/7. talk to me
column2: ask me for help. we can make a difference together if we share our stories and work on making this cruel world a better place. dm me!

column1: 217829;instagram;2018-11-23 23:10:19;FALSE;"“7 years ago i said “no” to staying inside my comfort zone after grad school in nyc
column2: and i took an opportunity to relocate again to europe-switzerland.  as an expat abroad and the only poc in my executive leadership team at my company’s international global hq
column5: and creating opportunities for others globally.i say “no” to the box many have tried to place me in based off my gender and race.  i’ve said “no” to pa state rape kit processing laws by meeting with my local senators
column7: to write and help pass comprehensive legislation.  i continue to say “no” to voter suppression that continues to happen in our african american communities (e.g. georgia
column9: “no” to the dakota access pipeline that destroys the land of my indigenous people
column10: “no” to my sisters and brothers’ voices and stories not being heard in the #metoo movement…we all have stories
column11: “no” to our stories not being heard in hollywood…i could go on forever….most importantly
column12: i say “yes” to love and creating spaces that are truly diverse and inclusive for everyone and supporting people and causes that are trying to achieve the same goal.

column1: thanks for asking to hear our voices.  let’s do this work together.” -@nik_nyc

column2: someone opened a door that should have remained closed much longer. the body suffered. the mind took a blow. and the whole world went upside down. innocence flew away. and loneliness settled.

column1: my work comes from my obsession with mouths. i cut them in the women magazines and then put them on pics i’ve taken from objects or places in cities. i then photograph this moment that will then disappear as i’ll remove the mouths to create other images. each ‘moment’ (each image) thus only exists in a pic gallery. it is as brief as a rape. but it’s a moment in time that will last forever in the brain. 🇫🇷 voici comment tout a commencé. quelqu’un a pris quelque chose qui ne lui appartenait pas. quelqu’un a ouvert une porte qui aurait dû rester fermée bien plus longtemps. le corps a souffert. l’esprit a pris un coup. et le monde s’est effondré. l’innocence s’est envolée. et la solitude s’est installée.
mon travail vient de mon obsession des bouches. je les découpe dans des magasines féminins et les place ensuite sur des photos que j’ai prises
column2: le plus souvent dans la rue. je photographie alors ce ‘moment’ qui n’existera plus jamais ailleurs que sur la pellicule
column3: en écho  au viol qui le plus souvent est furtif mais reste à jamais gravé dans la mémoire des victimes.  #droitsdesfemmes #iambecoming #womenrights #noviolencetowomen #stopalaviolencefaiteauxfemmes #jemarchele24 #photomontage #photography #collage #collageartwork #artexpression #noustoutes #metoo #metoomovement #readmylipsproject";;en;#droitsdesfemmes

column7: la faible présence des femmes dans le cinéma
column8: affadissant leurs vécus et leurs visions du monde
